4 Section 2. Section 2-15-143, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "2-15-143. Training and consultation Consultation and training -- duties of tribal liaison. (1)
6 When establishing a government-to-government relationship with tribal governments, a state agency shall:
7 (a) collaborate with tribal governments in the development of policies, agreements, administrative
8 rules, and program implementation that directly affect Indian tribes;
9 (b) consult with tribal governments as often as is required to address matters that have tribal
10 implications;
11 (c) develop a written consultation policy in coordination with representatives of each federally
12 recognized tribe in the state that is used by the agency for issues involving specific Indian tribes. A consultation
13 policy must be created by January July 1, 2026, and be updated as often as required to facilitate timely and
14 meaningful consultation, but no less than biannually annually.
15 (d) provide tribal governments in the state with a copy of the agency's initial consultation policy and
16 all subsequent updates to the policy;
17 (e) designate an agency employee by July 1, 2026, to act as a tribal liaison who reports directly to
18 the head of the state agency; and
19 (f) ensure that a tribal liaison receives regular trainings that assist in the liaison's job functions,
20 including but not limited to the training prescribed in subsection (4).
21 (2) The position of tribal liaison within a state agency is responsible for:
22 (a) assisting the state agency in developing and implementing state and agency policies that
23 promote effective communication and collaboration between the state agency and tribal governments;
24 (b) serving as a contact person with tribal governments and maintaining communication between
25 the state agency and affected tribal governments; and
26 (c) coordinating training of state agency employees in government-to-government relations that
27 includes at a minimum:
28 (i) effective communication and collaboration between state agencies and Indian tribes; and
